+------------------------------------+
|      Feature Editing Example       |
+------------------------------------+
      for Avatar Core Framework
 http://myavatareditor.com/avatarcore 


Description:
	This example shows how visual Feature representations (ArtSprites) can be
	interacted with on the screen by a user to manipulate the underlying 
	definition of an Avatar object (Feature Adjust objects).

Uses:
	Basic Avatar components (Avatar, Feature, Art, AvatarDisplay)
	XML (inline) parsing
	Feature parenting
	Feature Adjusts
	Mirror behaviors

Contents:
	FeatureEditing.fla (Required)
	FeatureEditing.html
	FeatureEditing.swf
	+ src
		FeatureEditing.as
		IFeatureTool.as
		MoveFeatureTool.as
		RotateFeatureTool.as
		ScaleFeatureTool.as

Versions:
	Language: ActionScript 3.0
	IDE: Flash CS4 (for FLA)
